metadata.name: color combinations #184
metadata.description:
the 'color combinations' series was developed as an exercise of combining colors from a single defined palette and the attempt to make all 15 selected colors being able to work within each other.

the constant pursuit for perfectionism made me design more than 200 tentatives of creating a perfect circle, and therefore the circle is the rarest output for the series.

i hope this series serves as a reference and inspire everyone out there.

2,340 possible combinations.
the closer the shape to the circle the rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%.
the bigger the shape the rarer - ranging from 30% to 20%.
beige and black colors are rarer - ranging from 100% to 5%

metadata.name: Phantoms #91
metadata.description:
Phantoms is a series of hazy memories of distant places. Some tranquil, others sinister, each scene is as much defined by what is revealed as by what remains unseen.

In this collection I aim to juxtapose hard and soft. Blocky shapes form the core of the compositions. Upon these surfaces, soft textures appear to flow and drip over the sides. Varying levels of opacity, lighting, and fog effects further soften the scenes to create an atmospheric, dream-like quality. By remaining semi-abstract, each of the color palettes are given the space to influence the mood dramatically.

metadata.name: Neighbours #29
metadata.description:
Binary neighbourliness based on a simple rule where if a block has the same binary value as its 3 neighbours they become friends.

How this works under the hood:
1. Hash determines grid size
2. Hash is also converted into an array of numbers from chunking the hashes.
3. Hash is converted to binary and a subset of the binary string is chosen according to a hashed numeric value based on the grid size
4. If a block has the same binary value as its 3 neighbours they all take on the same properties and turn red.


- radarboy3000 (November 2021)

metadata.name: Alleles #203
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Exploration of the information extracted from the provided genetic information suggests subject experiences intermittent occurences of grandiosity and a need for constant reassurance, yet also is capable of unusual [REDACTED] and abstract reasoning. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 170-175cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 81-92 years.
